<br>
**********************************************<br>
Greetings <br>
<br>
This is GM Crayson, thank you for emailing us. Actually we use the same<br>
contact that players use for the Dev Department. If I would forward your<br>
email the only one I have would be eqmail@soe.sony.com.For the most part<br>
Dev. does not respond to email that are redirect to them it however does not<br>
mean that they don't read them I know for a fact that they do and or none of<br>
the changes in everquest would have been done. Unfortunately they cannot<br>
change something ingame with only one or a few wanting the change, they<br>
would need a good portion of the fan base wanting the change then consider<br>
what the change will do to other aspects of the game. Your going about it<br>
the write way by using the contacts at the forums and the emails and how<br>
knows if enough of the players want the change maybe it will happend. If you<br>
have further questions or comments please email me at jtyler@soe.sony.com.<br>
<br>
Thank you for playing quest<br>
<br>
GM Crayson<br>
